The paper deals with computing shortest paths in a metric space, which is a common problem in robotics and motion planning. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with constructing a simplicial complex from a metric graph, which involves computational geometry, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) another likely sub-category. The algorithm presented in the paper requires only an abstract graph and a cost function, which suggests that it may fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the representation of metric spaces using simplicial complexes, which is a topic in cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing).
